The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves designing algorithms that make decisions based on incomplete information, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses objective functions and solution concepts, which are topics in both economics and machine learning (cs.EC and cs.LG).
